In distributing the following Scene into lines, we have adhered closely to the arrangement of B. Hermann, Rstschl, VVeise, and others, have their own metrical views, upon which it is quite unnecessary to enlarge.

1. multum sum et R, without any MS. authority.

2. C omits in pectus. The MSS. have institui. Reizius, R, W', and others, have adopted institi-vi for the sake of the metre.

3, 4. These two lines are bracketed by R as interpolations. 4. W, following Hermann, has volutavi eam rem.

5, 6. So the MSS. R is dissatisfied, and thus remodels them—

Hominem quoius rei similem esse arbitrarer [simulacrumque habere]. 8. edium B.
